Defendant Jesse R Ramirez in court, in custody, with attorney Eryn M Menden.   Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.   The defendant was sentenced to the following:

JAIL: 5 days, APPLY 5 DAYS CREDIT, for TIME SERVED;

FINE: $275.05 (to pay $40.84 per month commencing 1/1/16 or serve 9 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid as part of payment plan on fine. 

  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

  Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
